16/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A seminar on border management co-operation among the countries in Southeast Europe wrapped up in Skopje on Tuesday (15 June). 
Representatives from Macedonia, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro and Slovenia, as well as experts from NATO and the EU, took part in the event. 
Zoran Jovanovski, head of the Macedonian Border Police Force, said the transfer of border control from the army to police is proceeding according to plan. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 15/06/04)
